<p><a name="Movements" id="Movements"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Christian_left&amp;action=edit&amp;section=51" title="Edit section: Movements">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Movements</span></h3>
<p>A number of movements of the past had similarities to today's Christian Left:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Anabaptists" title="Anabaptists" class="mw-redirect">Anabaptists</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Fifth_Monarchy_Men" title="Fifth Monarchy Men" class="mw-redirect">Fifth Monarchists</a>, <a href="/wiki/Diggers" title="Diggers">Diggers</a>, <a href="/wiki/Religious_Society_of_Friends" title="Religious Society of Friends">Quakers</a></li>
<li>Heretical movements such as the <a href="/wiki/Cathars" title="Cathars" class="mw-redirect">Cathars</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Liberation_theology" title="Liberation theology">Liberation theology</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Lollard" title="Lollard" class="mw-redirect">Lollard</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Old_Catholic_Church" title="Old Catholic Church">Old-Catholicism</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Peace_churches" title="Peace churches">Peace churches</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Peasants%27_War" title="Peasants' War">German Peasants' War</a></li>
<li>Role of Christians in the <a href="/wiki/Peasants%27_Revolt" title="Peasants' Revolt">Peasants' Revolt</a> in <a href="/wiki/England" title="England">England</a>, See Lollard priest <a href="/wiki/John_Ball_(priest)" title="John Ball (priest)">John Ball</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Waldenses" title="Waldenses" class="mw-redirect">Waldenses</a></li>
</ul>
